The answer to (i) appears a confident yes, as several studies have shown that LLMs can be used as powerful components in textual information extraction [alt2019fine,chu2021knowfi,josifoski2022genie]. Yet such a usage still requires comprehensive efforts around data selection and preparation, information retrieval, and output consolidation, and thus, does not fundamentally transform the task.